18 WHEREAS, Iota Phi Theta Fraternity, Inc., is a historically African
19 American fraternity and was founded on Thursday, September 19, 1963, at
20 Morgan State University in Baltimore, Maryland; and
21
22 WHEREAS, Iota Phi Theta Fraternity, Inc., is currently the fifth
23 largest Black Greek-letter fraternity with over seventy-five thousand
24 (75,000) members worldwide; and
25
26 WHEREAS, today there are over three hundred fifty (350) undergraduate
27 and alumni chapters of Iota Phi Theta Fraternity, Inc., located in forty (40)
28 states, the District of Columbia, the Bahamas, Colombia, South Korea, and
29 Japan; and
30
31 WHEREAS, the State of Arkansas currently has five (5) undergraduate
32 chapters of Iota Phi Theta Fraternity, Inc., and two (2) alumni chapters; and
33
34 WHEREAS, Iota Phi Theta Fraternity, Inc., holds membership in the
35 National Pan-Hellenic Council, an umbrella organization commonly referred to
36 as the "Divine Nine", which is composed of international historically African
